epatitis specialist.<\\/p><p>The proposed recommendations are expected to become final later this year. <\\/p>\",\"35\":\"<p>CDC on Friday announced a proposal to recommend that all people born between 1945 to 1965 get tested for hepatitis C virus. Baby boomers comprise more than 2 million of the estimated 3.2 million Americans thought to have HCV, but many do not know they are infected. CDC officials hope testing all baby boomers will help 800,000 get treated and prevent more than 120,000 deaths.<\\/p>\"}}', '2015-06-09 00:16:45', '2015-06-09 00:16:45', '34bba79d-af71-4dfb-8053-6e9bbc727d0b');
